  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="body:1;5:9">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:1;6:8">This datapath involves the following path:</p>

    <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="ul:1;8:9">
      <li id="d1e82552" class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="li:1;9:25"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:2;9:28">MAPOTN(ODUflex.GFP) &lt;= =&gt; COREOTN (ODUflex)
      &lt;= =&gt; COPI (ODUflex &lt;-&gt; ILKN)</p></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:3;13:8">This datapath represents Node A or C where the ODUkP/PCK adaptation is
    represented and the ODUkP/ODUj-21 adaptation is in another device.
    Essentially only ODUflex.GFP exists within this device. <xref audience="DIGIG5_ROW" href="#Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo/MAP_CORE_SIFD_Datapath_ROW__ihi4tj4fo" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="xref:1;15:174" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 1</xref>
    represents this datapath through the device subsystems:</p>

    <note audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="note:1;18:35"><xref href="http://bby1dms01.pmc-sierra.internal/docmgmt/fileinfo.cfm?file_id=416475" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="xref:2;18:138"><?ditaot usertext?>
    http://bby1dms01.pmc-sierra.internal/docmgmt/fileinfo.cfm?file_id=416475
    </xref> tab : SourceSink Node Datapath 2</note>

    <fig audience="DIGIG5_ROW" id="MAP_CORE_SIFD_Datapath_ROW__ihi4tj4fo" class="- topic/fig " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="fig:1;22:75">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="title:2;23:14">MAP_CORE_COPI Datapath</title>

      <image href="../Graphics/pm5440_map_core_sifd_datapath.svg" placement="break" width="5.5in" class="- topic/image " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="image:1;25:100"/>
    </fig>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:4;28:8">The LCR steps for increase and decrease through the Interlaken path are
    not conducted with this device instead are conducted in node-level
    software. This device only is aware when G.HAO is entered and when BWR
    begins. But prior to ramp beginning, the customer must prepare their
    fabric to expect a ramp (that is, change any rate shapers, FIFOs,
    schedulers). This is usually done before relaying the NCS bit from this
    device.</p>

    <p audience="DIGIG5_NOKIA" class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:5;36:32">Through the FIC path, LCR of the FIC is
    conducted (i.e. FIFO resize/Knife-edge), but not exactly in the same
    protocol manner as the ODUkP/ODUj-21 adaptation function defined in
    G.798/G.7044. The method is proprietary to the FIC. The LCR steps are
    primarily there to do setup of the FIFOs and FIC-specific tribslots and
    any control plane negotiation that needs to be conducted through the
    proprietary FIC.</p>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:6;44:8">In BWR, the NCS bit is set in the TGPF and received in the RGFP. GMP
    special mode is realized by setting the SAR from OPSA mode to a hold-over
    mode.</p>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:7;48:8">The ramp itself is triggered at the ODUk Scheduler at MAPOTN after
    setting TGFP to insert the BWR_IND bit. <ph audience="DIGIG5_NOKIA" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="ph:1;49:73">In the
    egress direction (towards FIC), BWR_IND is set through the SAR and the it
    is picked up at SAR, which will commence the ramp according to the ramp
    rate, but with tracking of the ODUk Switch FIFO fill level. </ph>In the
    egress direction (towards the ILKN), no ramp towards ILKN is required; the
    ODUk SC ramp is sufficient. In the ingress direction (from the ILKN<ph audience="DIGIG5_NOKIA" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="ph:2;54:100"> or FIC</ph>), RFRM stage 4 picks up the BWR_IND
    bit inserted and sends it back to the SAR, which will commence the ramp
    according to the ramp rate, but with tracking of the ODUk Switch FIFO fill
    level.</p>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\05_Functional_Description\Topics\Source_Sink_Node_Datapath_2_hhi4tj4fo.xml" xtrc="p:8;59:8">Once the ramp is complete, both the SAR and ODUk Scheduler will issue a
    ‘ramp_done’ interrupt that will allow software to wrap up the G.HAO
    protocol.</p>
